    "body": "Possible ways of storing links to Figma:\r\n- directly in model (most straightforward way):\r\n```\r\n        ListElement {\r\n             title: \"BrowserSettings\"\r\n             figma: [\"https://www.figma.com/file/17fc13UBFvInrLgNUKJJg5/Kuba%E2%8E%9CDesktop?node-id=13653%3A447420\",\r\n                     \"https://www.figma.com/file/17fc13UBFvInrLgNUKJJg5/Kuba%E2%8E%9CDesktop?node-id=13653%3A447421\"]\r\n        }\r\n```\r\n- in a separate file (e.g. yaml). \r\n   - the benefit is that we could have a possibility to add links directly via Storybook without need to modify the source code. The file would be stored in source directory and could be committed to repo as other files. For QA team it could be more handy then. Possible file structure could be more or less like that:\r\n\r\n`figma-links.yaml`:\r\n```\r\nBrowserSettings:\r\n  - \"https://www.figma.com/file/17fc13UBFvInrLgNUKJJg5/Kuba%E2%8E%9CDesktop?node-id=13653%3A447420\"\r\n  - \"https://www.figma.com/file/17fc13UBFvInrLgNUKJJg5/Kuba%E2%8E%9CDesktop?node-id=13653%3A447421\"\r\nProfilePopup:\r\n  - \"https://www.figma.com/file/17fc13UBFvInrLgNUKJJg5/Kuba%E2%8E%9CDesktop?node-id=13653%3A447428\"\r\n```\r\n\r\n- directly in source code of components (e.g. assigned to some agreed property)\r\n\r\n@caybro @osmaczko @alexandraB99 @iurimatias wdyt?",
